ed vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}],"title":"MLNMultiPolyline","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNFillStyleLayer":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFillStyleLayer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders one or more filled (and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"optionally stroked) polygons on the map."}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNFillStyleLayer"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFillStyleLayer","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnfillstylelayer","title":"MLNFillStyleLayer","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointAnnotation":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a one-dimensional shape located at a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single geographical coordinate. Depending on how it is used, an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object is known as a point annotation or point shape. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point shape to represent a city at low zoom levels, an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"address at high zoom levels, or the location of a long press gesture."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","title":"MLNPointAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointannotation","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeSource":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","title":"MLNShapeSource","abstract":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" is a map content source that supplies vector shapes to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown on the map. The shapes may be instances of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or they may be defined by local or external"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GeoJSON"},{"type":"text","text":" code. A shape source is added to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" object along with an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" object. The vector style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layer defines the appearance of any content supplied by the shape source. You"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can update a shape source by setting its "},{"code":"shape","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"URL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNShapeSource"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapesource"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolylineFeature":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a polyline shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolylineFeature"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolylineFeature","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolylinefeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"title":"MLNMultiPolygon","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object, while the surrounding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group of disconnected but related buildings."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolygon"}]}}}